*** Comments
+ Presents techniques in CBT
+ Local Filtering:
  - Use each constraint as a filter for the domains of involved variables
  - We did that with refiners (maybe overdid it..)
+ Constraint propagation and enumeration:
  - Propagate constraints until fixpoint
  - If more than a single solution left, enumerate (<- here is one big
    difference)
+ Linear Relaxation
  - Convert program to linear inequalities that describe the entire state
    space
  - Allows handling of multiplication, division and modulo
+ Handling dysjunctions
  - First attempt to prove that one dysjunct is Unsat
  - If not, compute union 
  - Linear relaxation converts this to a convex-hull overapproximation
+ Slow convergence phenomenon
  - When the domain is pruned very slowly (usually from the edges)
  - I encountered that in the refiners as well!
