*** Comments
+ Survey of Gibbs samplers and proofs of adoptive Gibbs sampler correctness
+ Basic random Scan Gibbs Sampler:
  - Needs to know the full conditional distribution for each parameter!
  - Pick a vector of starting values (x01,x02,...x0d)
  - Pick an index i of a parameter to instantiate (at random)
  - Draw a value y from the distribution P(xi | x0(-i)) to get the next 
    value
+ Adoptive random Scan Gibbs Sampler:
  - Same as basic random scan except the index i you pick to instantiate
    can be picked w.r.t. information about values of x(n-1)
+ Metropolis withing Gibbs:
  - Instead of sampling from the full conditional, you perform a single
    Metropolis-Hastings step, ie:
  - After picking i, draw from a proposal distribution for i given X(n-1)
  - Calculate a quantity that shows if the new sample is "more likely". 
    That assumes either that we are "withing a ratio" of the posterior 
    distribution or (in the assymetric case) we know how to calculate 
    some conditional probs.
  - Proposal distributions can also be chosen adoptively
+ Additional conditions on ergoticity of the above algorithms and proofs  
