  - Constraint solving optimizations
  - Compact representation of program states
  - Search heuristics to get high coverage
+ Applied on real programs

+ Compact state representation
  - Copy-on-write at the object level
  - Ability to clone heap structure in constant time
+ Query optimizations
  - Expression rewriting like in compilers
  - Constraint Set simplification (rewriting in constraints)
  - Implied Value Concretization (solve deterministic constraints)
  - Constraint Independence
  - Counter-example Cache <- This is something we could use/modify as an idea
+ State Scheduling - heuristics
  - Random path selection 
  - Coverage-Optimized search

+ Environment Modeling 
  - Return all possible values of a system call rather than a concrete run

+ Very promising evaluation
+ Still, it couldn't even do a simple IFC LLNI
