*** Comments
+ Goal: Formally verified translation from a high level (ML like) language to
  a constraint solving system.
+ Goal of FocalTest in general: Verifiably MC/DC compliant testing tool

- MC/DC is a standard structural coverage criterion.
- It is used for critical applications "makes airplanes keep flying"
- It is however relatively easy to "cheat" (The Effect of Program and Model
  Structure on MC/DC Test Adequacy Coverage - ICSE '08)

- They present a translation from an ML like language to a constraint system.
- They use an intermediate language (FMON).
- The translation from Focalize to FMON is proved correct (sound and complete) 
  but the proof is in a PhD thesis written in French. (Not hard to believe 
  this translation though)
- This paper is mainly about translating FMON to their target language of 
  constraints.
- They don't handle higher-order functions (they have a translation but 
  claim the proof is too hard)
- TODO: Another assumption has to do with the "correct translation from MC/DC
  compliant values on decisions to simple decision (T/F) values". I'm not sure
  I understand what this means in practice...

- The translation itself is pretty straightforward (with handwritten
  constraints for things like match) 
- The proofs are (claimed to be) induction proofs and the "hard parts" are
  said to be dealing with fresh variables in let-like constructs. 

- It really is "a first step". Not really much to do with Zoe's framework
  after all. 

