  url       = {http://publications.lib.chalmers.se/records/fulltext/local_99387.pdf},
}
Maxime: The idea is to use parametricity to account for the fact that
testing a polymorphic property can be done by specializing to given
types (typically nat), without loosing counter-examples. There may be
an interesting story to extend that to dependent types.
CH: very interestingly, they can often test a much simpler property
than just instantiating all types with nat in the original property
(e.g. all [1,2,..,n] lists vs. all lists of nats)
CH: not clear whether they ever implemented this, although it seems it
should help in practice

Q: Could parametricity also be used for better testing dependently
   typed functions?

